{{Infobox badminton event |name = 2006 Thomas & Uber Cups Preliminaries for Africa |image = |size = |caption = |dates = 19-23 February 2006 |number_edition = 2 |level = |prize_money = |other = |venue = National Badminton Centre |location = [[Rose Hill, Mauritius]] |previous = [[2004 Thomas & Uber Cups Preliminaries for Africa|2004]] |next = [[2008 Thomas & Uber Cups Preliminaries for Africa|2008]] }}
The '''2006 [[Africa Continental Team Badminton Championships|Thomas & Uber Cups Preliminaries for Africa]]''' were held in [[Rose Hill, Mauritius]], between 19-23 February and organised by Mauritius Badminton Association.<ref>{{cite news|title=Le retrait du Nigeria profitera aux autres |url=http://www.lexpress.mu/article/le-retrait-du-nigeria-profitera-aux-autres |website=www.lexpress.mu |publisher=[[L'Express (Mauritius)|L'Express]] |accessdate=29 November 2016 |language=French}}</ref> [[South Africa national badminton team|South Africa]] was the defending champion in men's and women's team events. This tournament serves as qualification stage for African countries for the [[2006 Thomas & Uber Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Maurice-Afrique du Sud : l?ultime étape |url=http://www.lexpress.mu/article/maurice-afrique-du-sud-lultime-%C3%A9tape |website=www.lexpress.mu |publisher=[[L'Express (Mauritius)|L'Express]] |accessdate=29 November 2016 |language=French}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Thomas et Uber Cup zone Afrique |url=http://www.africa-badminton.com/A%20JEUX%20AFRICA/thomasetubercup.htm |website=www.africa-badminton.com |publisher=[[Badminton Confederation of Africa]]|accessdate=29 November 2016|language=French}}</ref> South Africa men's and women's team qualified to compete at the 2006 Thomas & Uber Cup held in [[Japan]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Badminton : Thomas Cup, Uber Cup et les Internationaux de Maurice-Une médaille d'argent et trois bronze pour les Seychellois |url=http://www.nation.sc/article.html?id=213003 |website=www.nation.sc |publisher=[[Seychelles Nation]]|accessdate=29 November 2016|language=French}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Badminton-Eight local players for two international competitions |url=http://www.nation.sc/article.html?id=212927 |website=www.nation.sc |publisher=[[Seychelles Nation]]|accessdate=29 November 2016}}</ref>
