The '''Best U.S. Female Olympian [[ESPY Award]]''' has been presented annually since [[2009 in sports|2009]] to the [[sportswoman]] or [[team sports|team]] affiliated with the [[United States Olympic Committee]] and contesting [[List of sports|sport]] [[international]]ly adjudged to be the best. The award serves in practice to replace the [[Best Female Olympic Performance ESPY Award]], which was presented in [[2005 in sports|2005]], and the [[Best U.S. Olympian ESPY Award]] presented in 2006.
[[Voting|Balloting]] for the award is undertaken by [[fan (aficionado)|fan]]s over the [[Internet]] from amongst between three and five choices selected by the ESPN Select Nominating Committee, and the award is conferred in June to reflect performance and achievement over the twelve months previous.
