{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}} {{Use British English|date=March 2017}} [[File:British Cycling Hall of Fame inductees (7644751518).jpg|thumb|British Cycling Hall of Fame at the [[Manchester Velodrome]]]] [[File:Tom Simpson certificate in the British Cycling Hall Of Fame.jpg|upright|thumb|[[Tom Simpson]]'s certificate in the British Cycling Hall of Fame]] The '''British Cycling Hall of Fame''' was established in 2009 as part of [[British Cycling]]'s 50th anniversary celebrations.<ref name="BChalloffame">{{cite web| url=http://www.britishcycling.org.uk/news/article/bc20091216-Hall-of-fame-fifty| title=50 Cycling Heroes Named in British Cycling's Hall of Fame| publisher=[[British Cycling]]| date=17 December 2009}}</ref>
On 17 December 2009, the names of fifty people involved in the sport to be inducted into the British Cycling Hall of Fame were announced. The selection panel, whose job it was to whittle the names down from 300 nominations, consisted of [[Brian Cookson]], [[William Fotheringham]], [[Robert Garbutt]], [[Peter King (cyclist)|Peter King]], [[Victoria Pendleton]] and [[Hugh Porter]].<ref name="BChalloffame" /><ref>{{cite web|title=British Cycling Hall of Fame – 2010 Inductees|url=http://www.britishcycling.org.uk/50th-anni/article/bcst-British-Cycling-Hall-of-Fame-2010-Inductees|work=[[British Cycling]]|accessdate=25 April 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130509081655/http://www.britishcycling.org.uk/50th-anni/article/bcst-British-Cycling-Hall-of-Fame-2010-Inductees#|archive-date=9 May 2013|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The inaugural induction ceremony was held on 20 February 2010 at [[Manchester Central Convention Complex|Manchester Central]], hosted by television present [[Dermot Murnaghan]].<ref>{{Cite web | url = http://www.cyclingweekly.com/news/latest-news/british-cycling-hall-of-fame-nominees-inducted-at-gala-dinner-62963| title = British Cycling Hall of Fame nominees inducted at Gala Dinner| work = [[British Cycling]] | accessdate = 12 June 2017 | date = 22 February 2010}}</ref>
