{{Infobox sports team | name = Chartres ASTT | color1 = white | color2 = #0431B4 | logo = | logo_size = | alt = | caption = | full_name = Association Sportive de Tennis de Table de Chartres | nicknames = | founded = 2003 | league = [[Pro A (men's table tennis)|Pro A]] | arena = Complexe Sportif Rosskopf | city = [[Chartres]], [[France]] | president = Loïc Bréhu | coach = Calin Toma | members = 260 | website = {{Official website|http://www.chartres-astt.fr}} }} '''Association Sportive de Tennis de Table de Chartres''' is a [[table tennis]] club based in [[Chartres]], [[France]]. One of the best teams in the country in the recent years, it won the French top division [[Pro A (men's table tennis)|Pro A]] both in 2012 and 2013. Chartres also has respectable results in continental competitions, having won the [[ETTU Cup]] in 2011 and finishing runner-up in the [[European Champions League (table tennis)|European Champions League]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ettu.org/mens-european-champions-league/clubs/chartres-astt/|title=Chartres ASTT Team Profile|publisher=[[European Table Tennis Union]]|accessdate=20 November 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131204182502/http://www.ettu.org/mens-european-champions-league/clubs/chartres-astt/|archivedate=4 December 2013|df=}}</ref>
