[[File:Stokescenter.JPG|right|thumb]]
'''DeGol Arena''' is a 3,500-seat multi-purpose [[arena]] in [[Loretto, Pennsylvania]]. It is home to the [[Saint Francis University]] Red Flash men's and women's basketball teams and the men's and women's volleyball teams<ref>http://sfuathletics.com/facilities/?id=3</ref>. It opened in 1972. The 1991 [[Northeast Conference]] men's basketball tournament was held there.

The arena is the centerpiece of the [[Maurice Stokes]] Athletic Center.

