'''Mogo Wheelchairs''' is an Australian manufacturer of sporting [[wheelchairs]] established by Michael Callahan who competed in [[wheelchair basketball]] for [[Australia at the 1984 Summer Paralympics]] and [[Australia at the 1992 Summer Paralympics|1992 Summer Paralympics]].<ref>[http://www.parliament.nsw.gov.au/prod/parlment/hansart.nsf/V3Key/LA20001012004 NSW Hansard, 12 October 2000, Sydney 2000 Paralympic Games]</ref><ref name="smh2000">{{cite news <!-- illegal copy? http://www.biceps.com.au/biceps-articles/2000/8/31/he-got-game/ --> | newspaper = Sydney Morning Herald | title = He got game | date = 31 August 2000 | page = 26 | author = Michelle Griffin }}</ref><ref>{{cite newspaper | title = Wheelchair gives Jason an edge: | newspaper = [[The Nelson Mail]], [[Nelson, New Zealand]] | date = 20 September 2000 | page = 23 }}</ref><ref name="aboutus"/>

==Origins==
Callahan wasn't able to find suitable chairs for competitive wheelchair basketball, and started building his own in the early 1980s.<!-- SMH says 1984; Mogo says 1982 --><ref name="smh2000"/><ref name="aboutus"/> In 2000 Callahan reported to [[Sydney Morning Herald]] that his company was building 600 to 700 chairs a year at around [[Australian Dollar|AUD]] 2000 per chair, and almost all of Australia's wheelchair basketball team was using his chairs.<ref name="smh2000"/>

Mogo pioneered the inclusion of a fifth wheel that is now standard in wheelchair basketball.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wheelchairbasketball.ca/en/content.aspx?id=4990 |title=The Wheelchair : |publisher=Wheelchairbasketball.ca |date= |accessdate=2013-06-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.livestrong.com/article/10066-smart-shopping-basketball-wheelchairs/ |title=Basketball Wheelchairs |publisher=Livestrong.Com |date= |accessdate=2013-06-08}}</ref>

==Advocacy==
Double amputee, Paralympian and public speaker Matt Glowacki is their advocate in the United States.<ref>{{cite news | title = Guest lecturer to address diversity on 'south park' | newspaper = US Fed News Service | date = 21 Oct 2009 | url = http://spider.flcc.edu/wordpress/?p=1758 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20100609131610/http://spider.flcc.edu/wordpress/?p=1758 | archivedate = 2010-06-09 }}</ref><ref name="aboutus">{{cite web|url=http://www.mogowheelchairs.com.au/aboutus.php |title=About Mogo Wheelchairs :: 100% Australian custom made wheelchair |publisher=Mogowheelchairs.com.au |date= |accessdate=2013-06-08}}</ref>

