{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Sheikhupura Stadium | country = Pakistan | location = [[Sheikhupura]], Punjab, [[Pakistan]] | image = | establishment = | seating_capacity = 15,000 | owner = [[Pakistan Cricket]] | end1 = | end2 = | international = yes | firsttestdate = 17 October | firsttestyear = 1996 | firsttesthome = Pakistan | firsttestaway = Zimbabwe | lasttestdate = 17 October | lasttestyear = 1997 | lasttesthome = Pakistan | lasttestaway = South Africa | firstodidate = 22 November | firstodiyear = 1998 | firstodihome = Pakistan | firstodiaway = Zimbabwe | lastodidate = 2 February | lastodiyear = 2008 | lastodihome = Pakistan | lastodiaway = Zimbabwe | firstt20idate = | firstt20iyear = | firstt20ihome = | firstt20iaway = | lastt20idate = | lastt20iyear = | lastt20ihome = | lastt20iaway = | year1 = | club1 = | year2 = | club2 = | date = 29 November | year = 2016 | source = http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/ground/59016.html ESPNcricinfo }}
'''Sheikhupura Stadium''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Sheikhupura]], [[Pakistan]]. It is currently used mostly for [[cricket]] matches. The stadium holds 15,000 people and hosted its first Test match in 1996, when Pakistan played [[Zimbabwe national cricket team|Zimbabwe]].<ref name="Dawn">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1319194 |title=Stadium stories: Famous Pakistan cricket grounds |accessdate=11 March 2017 |work=Dawn}}</ref> This was followed by another test a year later between Pakistan and [[South Africa]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Sheikhupura Stadium |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/ground/59016.html |work=ESPN Cricinfo |date=17 June 2011 |accessdate=17 June 2011 }}</ref>
Sheikhupura Stadium has hosted two one-day internationals so far, both between Pakistan and Zimbabwe, both teams winning a match.
